        'John Dalton developed the modern atomic theory in 1803, and Ernest Rutherford discovered the structure of the atom in 1909 — a tiny nucleus surrounded by orbiting electrons.',
        'Atoms are mostly empty space; if an atom were the size of a football stadium, the nucleus at the centre would be the size of a pea, with electrons orbiting in the stands.',
